&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join a well-motivated and evolving team on the Critcal care Unit at Alder Hey Children&#39;s Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The appointed ANP will work alongside the existing ANP&#39;s and Consultants to provide seven day cover. ANP&#39;s are expected to manage the patients admitted to the HDU with input from the HDU/PICU Consultants and speciality teams as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a General HDU and admitted patients include Cardiology, General and Speciality Medical and Surgical patients, including post-operative patients. The ANP will be supported to develop skills and knowledge to manage these patients including specialist skills such as ultrasound guided vascular access and intra-hospital patient transfer. However, a large proportion of the admitted children will require ventilatory support and experience in acute or long term ventilation would be essential.&lt;/p&gt;
